// A table cell may carry its own `{ }` style block for a colour or weight
// [SPEC 8] — `"Apple" { color: --red-ink }`. It stays a bare text leaf (a box
// child is only needed to place or link a cell). `fmt` re-emits the block and
// lifts that row out of the aligned grid; the plain rows keep their columns.

|table#stock| "Stock" { columns: 110 70 90; } [
  "Item"  "Qty" "State"
  "Apple" "12"  "fresh"
  "Mango" "3"   "ripe"
  "Lime" "0" "out" { color: --red-ink; font-weight: bold; }
]
